            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Shutdown-resistant messaging.</h1>
            <p class="lead">Stay connected without the internet.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container py-5">
        <section>
            <h2 class="section-header">About Dash Chat</h2>
            <p class="mt-4">We’re developing an offline-first, encrypted, peer-to-peer messaging app specifically designed for communities experiencing internet shutdowns, low connectivity, natural disasters, or unreliable network conditions.</p>
            <p>With authoritarianism and network interference increasing worldwide, secure and sovereign communication without dependence on stable internet is becoming essential yet remains a challenge.</p>
            <p>Dash Chat operates independently from centralized servers or stable internet, built directly with communities most affected by network disruptions, ensuring encrypted communication precisely when it matters most.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-5">
            <h2 class="section-header">Current Status & Next Steps</h2>
            <h5 class="mt-4">Already completed:</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ Selected core technology (Holochain)</li>
                <li>✅ Developed multi-device synchronization prototype</li>
                <li>✅ Began detailed community-focused research</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>Upcoming (MVP, Jan–Dec 2025):</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>☐ User research and co-design workshops</li>
                <li>☐ Build and field-test prototype (offline, secure backups, encryption)</li>
                <li>☐ Refine based on direct feedback</li>
                <li>☐ iOS, Networking with Iroh, File Sharing, Location Sharing</li>
                <li>☐ Disappearing messages, Hidden locked chats, Emojis, Search, Reactions</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>Future Development:</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>☐ Raspberry Pi always-online nodes, Emergency relay mode</li>
                <li>☐ Multimedia messaging, Advanced encryption</li>
                <li>☐ Localization and global adaptation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-5">
            <h2 class="section-header">User Research & Design Approach</h2>
            <p class="mt-4">We’re conducting extensive user research and UI/UX design with Decent Design, supported by OTF’s User Experience and Discovery Lab. Our research carefully addresses specific needs, contexts, and user priorities, ensuring we develop technology transparently and responsibly.</p>
            <p>If your community or organization would like to participate, please reach out securely via <a href="#">this form</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-5">
            <h2 class="section-header">Why Another Messaging App?</h2>
            <ul class="mt-4">
                <li><strong>Signal, Telegram, Matrix:</strong> Fail during internet shutdowns.</li>
                <li><strong>Delta Chat:</strong> Resilient, but dependent on email infrastructure.</li>
                <li><strong>Briar:</strong> No iOS, multi-device, backups, or multimedia.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Dash Chat aims to recreate main-net chat experiences reliably on local networks, prioritizing usability and security.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-5">
            <h2 class="section-header">Who It’s For</h2>
            <ul class="mt-4">
                <li>Communities facing poor or disrupted internet infrastructure</li>
                <li>Villages in the global south, disaster-affected communities</li>
                <li>Protestors, journalists, human rights defenders, digital security practitioners</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mt-5">
            <h2 class="section-header">Team & Advisors</h2>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>Team:</strong> Eric Bear (Lead), Guillem Cordoba, Michael Dougherty (Engineering), Viktor Zaunders (Operations), Jun (User Research)</p>
            <p><strong>Advisors:</strong> Andreas Dzialocha (p2panda, Delta Chat), Holmes Wilson (Quiet), Stacey Tsui (Security trainer)</p>
        </section>

